{"fetchedAt":1782281011447,"updatedDate":"15.06.2026","title":null,"summary":"By June, following the February 28, 2026 closure of the Strait of Hormuz, outbound shipments of crude oil, LNG, and fertilizers had effectively ground to a halt. Crude oil flows were down 95%, LNG 99%, and fertilizer-related cargoes 94%. Before the conflict, these flows accounted for roughly 20–33% of global seaborne volumes in their respective categories. Inbound agricultural shipments into the Persian Gulf initially held up as pre-closure cargoes continued to discharge, but that buffer had largely run out by June. Shipments were down 80–85% from April levels, while volumes had fallen 78–83%. Any meaningful recovery across these commodity flows now depends entirely on the resumption of new transits through the Strait.","paragraphs":[],"status":"closed","charts":[{"label":"crude_oil_outbound","title":"Crude Oil Outbound Shipments","series":[{"date":"June-01-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-02-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-03-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-04-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-05-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-06-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-07-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-08-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-09-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-10-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-11-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-12-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-13-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-14-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-15-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-16-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-17-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-18-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-19-2026","value":14.49953448838825},{"date":"June-20-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-21-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-22-2026","value":0},{"date":"June-23-2026","value":0},{"date":"May-26-2026","value":0},{"date":"May-27-2026","value":0},{"date":"May-28-2026","value":0},{"date":"May-29-2026","value":0},{"date":"May-30-2026","value":0},{"date":"May-31-2026","value":0}]},{"label":"lng_outbound","title":"LNG Outbound Shipments","series":[{"da